<br>
Argo management is a hugh issue while we play this game everquest.  The biggest issue we have here is lack of understanding on how other class's work and general idoit behaviour.  I do not expect everyone to be an expert on every class, but I do expect them to be an expert in their class if they are 61+.  Common sense is over rated also.<br>
<br>
If a shaman/enchanter slows a mob while standing max distance half way up a mountain... who's faunt is it you could not control Argo?<br>
<br>
If a Monk/Rogue/ranger are using procing weapons with high taunt value... is it your problem they get smacked on?    Most of the time I refuse to even taunt it back when i see one of these class procing and gaining argo.<br>
<br>
If a Pallie/SK are casting every available spell they got during a battle is argo control a warrior issue?<br>
<br>
If a wizzie (standing up on the wall with the shaman) decides to nuke their ass off, but you see no concussion spells between nukes... who is at fault?<br>
<br>
Mages/Necro's that are 61+ that still sit and /pet attack.  I still chuckle when i see em die in under a second  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
There are numerous other little things that could be mentioned.  I am just trying to make a point though, not here to educate.<br>
<br>
You don't have a horse, you don't like horses?  Go back to exping pre pop.<br>
<br>
I for 1 have no issues with argo control as a warrior, I only have an issue with argo management from others.<br>
<br>
Marshall Dashaa 65 Overlord - Drinal<br>
