<br>
I have 325 AXP.  I have every offensive/defensive AA a warrior can have.  I have 2 weapons with sub 20 delay and stun procs and I still lose aggro.  <br>
<br>
Now, I don't lose aggro very much in any exp group I have been in in recent memory.  The occasional SoS crit early on will grab it from me sometimes if I havent proc'd enough.  So yeah, killing random Valor_Mob01 or random Plane_of_Fire_Mob02, I hold the aggro pretty well. <br>
<br>
Wait, what did I say?  If I haven't proc'd enough.  That is basically my taunt.  My procs.  DPS is a decent taunt in a normal exp group and will hold aggro to a fair extent.  Get 60 people hammering, nuking and healing and you better be procing if you are gonna keep that aggro.<br>
<br>
Is it my job to control aggro?  Yes and no.  Everyone has a responsibility to control their aggro to some degree.  <br>
<br>
The questions I guess should really be, should I have to work so hard to do what a SK or Pal can do with ease?  <br>
<br>
I am all for the Knight classes being powerful.  I don't need to do rogue DPS.  I don't need to be able to crank out 5400 crits like a wizard.  The one thing I would like to do is be able to hold aggro without having to pray to the Random Number God as often.<br>
<br>
Everyone is gonna lose aggro sometimes, I understand this and expect it.  I just don't like the feeling that I am constantly trying to swim upstream when my raidmates are doing the same thing I am, playing their class.<br>
<br>
